column22: While I had moments of questioning life's worth, I still had some optimism and hope for the future. It wasn't a total feeling of life being worthless.
column23: It was hard for me to wind down and relax after a long day of studying and working. I often felt restless and had trouble quieting my mind.
column24: I did not have difficulty swallowing. Swallowing was a normal and effortless process for me.
column25: Although I did have moments when I didn't find enjoyment in things, there were still activities that brought me pleasure. It wasn't a complete inability to derive joy from anything.
column26: I did not notice any abnormal action of my heart in the absence of physical exertion. My heartbeat was regular and didn't cause any concern.
column27: While I had moments of feeling down-hearted and blue, it wasn't a constant state. I had periods of feeling more optimistic and happy.
column28: I did feel irritable at times, but it wasn't a pervasive mood. I could manage my irritability and not let it affect all aspects of my life.
column29: I did not feel close to panic. I didn't experience any overwhelming feelings of panic or anxiety.
column30: It was often difficult for me to calm down after something upset me. It took me a while to regain my composure and let go of the negative emotions.
column31: I did not fear being "thrown" by trivial tasks. I felt confident in my ability to handle unfamiliar situations.
column32: While I did have moments of lacking enthusiasm, there were still things that sparked my interest and passion. It wasn't a complete inability to feel enthusiastic.
column33: I found it challenging to tolerate interruptions to my work or study. I preferred to stay focused and uninterrupted to maintain productivity.
column34: I had periods of being in a state of nervous tension, but it wasn't a constant or overwhelming feeling. There were moments of calm and relaxation as well.
column35: While I had moments of self-doubt and feeling inadequate, I still believed that I had worth as a person. It wasn't a complete feeling of being worthless.
column36: I was often intolerant of anything that kept me from getting on with my work or research. It was frustrating to have interruptions or delays that affected my productivity.
column37: I did not feel terrified. I didn't experience any extreme or irrational fear.
column38: While there were moments when I questioned the future, there were still things that gave me hope and a sense of purpose. It wasn't a complete feeling of hopelessness.
column39: While I had moments of contemplating life's meaning, I still found some meaning and fulfillment in my work and relationships. It wasn't a total feeling of life being meaningless.
column40: I did get agitated at times, but it wasn't a constant or overwhelming feeling. I could manage my agitation and calm myself down.
column41: Although I had some worries about panicking and embarrassing myself, it didn't consume my thoughts or hinder my daily functioning. It was a manageable concern.
column42: I did not experience any trembling in my hands or other parts of my body. I didn't have any noticeable trembling.
column43: While I did have moments of finding it difficult to initiate tasks, I still managed to overcome that inertia and get things done. It wasn't a complete lack of initiative.
